ZH: 他们用裹尸布把尸体包裹起来。
EN: They wrap the corpses in shrouds.
ZH: 裹尸布是用来包裹尸体的特殊布料。
EN: Shroud is a special fabric used to wrap corpses.
ZH: 老祖宗们通常会使用裹尸布作为丧葬的准备。
EN: Our ancestors used to use shrouds for funeral preparations.
ZH: 这个玛莎拉蒂车上覆盖着一层黑色的裹尸布。
EN: There is a layer of black shroud covering this Maserati car.
ZH: 在这个传统的文化中，裹尸布被视为非常吉祥的礼物。
EN: In this traditional culture, shrouds are regarded as very auspicious gifts.
ZH: 他小心翼翼地展开了裹尸布，露出了一具完整的尸体。
EN: He carefully unfolded the shroud, revealing a complete corpse.
ZH: 这块裹尸布上的图案非常精美，仿佛是一件艺术品。
EN: The pattern on this shroud is exquisitely made, as if it were a piece of art.
ZH: 裹尸布往往是白色的，象征着宁静和纯洁。
EN: Shrouds are often white in color, symbolizing tranquility and purity.
ZH: 他将尸体从裹尸布中取出，进行了细致的检查。
EN: He took out the body from the shroud and conducted a thorough examination.
ZH: 起初，他们只能看到裹尸布下面的模糊轮廓。
EN: At first, they could only see the vague silhouette under the shroud.
ZH: 裹尸布上绣着细小的花纹，给人一种庄严的感觉。
EN: There are embroidered delicate patterns on the shroud, giving a solemn feeling.
ZH: 这块裹尸布的质地非常柔软，触感舒适。
EN: The texture of this shroud is very soft and comfortable to touch.
ZH: 他在裹尸布上挂上了许多鲜花，以示对逝者的怀念。
EN: He hung many flowers on the shroud as a tribute to the deceased.
ZH: 裹尸布上的装饰物是由亲人精心制作的，以示对逝者的痛惜之情。
EN: The decorations on the shroud were carefully made by loved ones as a sign of mourning.
ZH: 裹尸布包裹着亡者的遗体，让人感到肃穆和庄重。
EN: The shroud envelops the body of the deceased, creating a solemn and solemn atmosphere.
ZH: 这件裹尸布堪称是现代艺术品，在展览中备受瞩目。
EN: This shroud can be regarded as a modern artwork and has received much attention in exhibitions.
ZH: 老太太将裹尸布小心地放入纸盒中，保存以备将来需要。
EN: The old lady carefully placed the shroud in a box for future use.
ZH: 男孩拿起裹尸布，试图用它变成一件超级英雄的斗篷。
EN: The boy picked up the shroud, trying to turn it into a cape for a superhero.
ZH: 裹尸布代表着生命的终结和阴间的归宿。
EN: The shroud represents the end of life and the destination of the afterlife.
